com.metreeca.rdf.services

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metreeca.rdf.services.Graph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RDF4JMemory, RDF4JNative, RDF4JRemote, RDF4JSPARQL, Stardog, Virtuoso

    public abstract class Graph
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Graph store.

    Manages task execution on an RDF repository.

    Nested task executions on the same graph store from the same thread will share the same connection to the backing RDF repository through a ThreadLocal context variable.

      • configure

        @SafeVarargs
public static <M extends Message<M>,O extends Operation> O configure(M message,
                                                                                  O operation,
                                                                                  BiConsumer<M,O>... customizers)
        Configures standard bindings for SPARQL message filters.

        Configures the following pre-defined bindings for the target SPARQL operation:

        variable value
        ?time an xsd:dateTime literal representing the execution system time with millisecond precision
        ?this the focus item of the filtered message
        ?stem the namespace of the IRI bound to the this variable
        ?name the local name of the IRI bound to the this variable
        ?task the HTTP method of the original request
        ?base the base IRI of the original request
        ?item the focus item of the original request
        ?user the IRI identifying the user submitting the original request or RDF.NIL if no user is authenticated

        If the target message is a response, the following additional bindings are configured:

        variable value
        ?code the HTTP status code of the filtered response
        Type Parameters:
        M - the type f the message to be filtered
        O - the type of the SPARQL operation to be configured
        Parameters:
        message - the message to be filtered
        operation - the SPARQL operation executed by the filter
        customizers - optional custom configuration setters for the SPARQL operation
        Returns:
        the input operation with standard bindings and optional custom configurations applied
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any argument is null or if customizers contains null values

      • auto

        public static Function<Request,String> auto()
        Creates a sequential auto-incrementing slug generator.

        Warning / SPARQL doesn't natively support auto-incrementing ids: auto-incrementing slug calls are partly serialized in the system graph database using an internal lock object; this strategy may fail for distributed containers or external concurrent updates on the SPARQL endpoint, causing requests to fail with an Response.InternalServerError or Response.Conflict status code.

        Returns:
        a slug generator returning an auto-incrementing numeric id unique to the focus item of the request

      • exec

        public Graph exec(Consumer<RepositoryConnection> task)
        Executes a task inside a transaction on this graph store.

        If a transaction is not already active on the shared repository connection, begins one at the isolation level required by this store and commits it on successful task completion; if the task throws an exception, the transaction is rolled back and the exception rethrown; in either case, no action is taken if the transaction was already terminated inside the task.

        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed; takes as argument a connection to the backing repository of this graph store
        Returns:
        this graph store
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if task is null

      • exec

        public <V> V exec(Function<RepositoryConnection,V> task)
        Executes a task inside a transaction on this graph store.

        If a transaction is not already active on the shared repository connection, begins one at the isolation level required by this store and commits it on successful task completion; if the task throws an exception, the transaction is rolled back and the exception rethrown; in either case no action is taken if the transaction was already closed inside the task.

        Type Parameters:
        V - the type of the value returned by task
        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed; takes as argument a connection to the backing repository of this graph store
        Returns:
        the value returned by task
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if task is null or returns a null value
